Records often have an empty body. But the (otherwise very useful) warning "undocumented empty block" is a bit annoying:

                Instead of writing

                private static record Point(int x, int y) {}

                you need

                private static record Point(int x, int y) {
                // record
                }

                to get rid of that warning.

                Maybe we need two warnings:

                - undocumented empty block (strict)
                - undocumented empty block

Created attachment 287394
                The source with manually adjusted layout as it should probably look like

                Switch expression formatting is broken when the switch expression appears in a lambda in a method chain:

                Stream.of(1, 2).map(it -) switch (it) {
                case 1 -) "one";
                case 2 -) "two";
                default -) {
                if (it ( 0) {
                throw new IllegalArgumentException("A negative value.");
                }

                yield it.toString();
                }
                }).forEach(System.out::println);


                This layout was produced by the Eclipse built-in formatter, but I tried it with other formatters and the results were similar: the whole switch was aligned
                according to the current left indentation.

